00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
This here is a radon test kit.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Okay, I'll be putting them everywhere.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
And please don't throw these out.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
This is a radon test kit.

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Please don't throw these out.

6
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,000
See them all over the office.

7
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Toby has been leaving radon kits everywhere,

8
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
like he owns the place.

9
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,000
The first time I threw mine away,

10
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,000
I thought it was an ant trap.

11
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
But I figured I'd rather live with ants

12
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,000
than with this creepy little disk.

13
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:33,000
The second time, I thought it was one of those,

14
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:36,000
you know, the things you turn over and it moves,

15
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,000
like a cow thing.

16
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
But upon closer examination,

17
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
it was another ant trap, so I threw it away.

18
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:48,000
And the third time, I did it out of spite.

19
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Come on, Michael, you're interrupting.

20
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
You're kidding me! God!

21
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,000
You say radon is silent but deadly,

22
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,000
and then you expect me not to make farting noises with my mouth?

23
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,000
What is this?

24
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Sit down.

25
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,000
You know what? We're not going to die of radon.

26
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
We're going to die of boredom.

27
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Right?

28
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
And if I had a gun with two bullets,

29
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,000
and I was in a room with Hitler, bin Laden, and Toby,

30
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:11,000
I would shoot Toby twice.

31
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,000
No.

32
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Okay.

33
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,000
You were being really funny, and then you went too far.

34
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
I would kill bin Laden and then Toby.

35
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,000
No.

36
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Okay, geniuses, how would you do it?

37
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Curve the bullet like in my favorite James McAvoy film,

38
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Wadid.

39
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
All that does is help you shoot around things.

40
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Is there a curtain rod in the room?

41
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,000
I don't know.

42
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,000
How about make believe Lan-Ez anything you want?

43
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Stanley, please, this is serious.

44
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Is this the thing where they use an icicle so there's no evidence?

45
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Yes.

46
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Re-stab Toby through the heart with an icicle?

47
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,000
The bullet-two bullet thing is a red herring.

48
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Here's how you do it.

49
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,000
You line them all up, you take one bullet,

50
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,000
shoot them all through the throat at the same time.

51
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Watch this.

52
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Phyllis, you're Hitler. Come up here.

53
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Toby, you're Toby.

54
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Andy, you're bin Laden.

55
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Line up.

56
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,000
I don't want her to.

57
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Throat's together.

58
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Toby, just do it.

59
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Toby, come on.

60
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Oh, God.

61
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Ready?

62
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,000
One bullet and boom.

63
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Yeah, that works.

64
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,000
It worked.
